              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Silicon detectors were oriented so that they",
                "would detect coincident pairs of fission fragments",
                "from compound nuclei recoiling downstream from the",
                "target. Fragments from prompt fission events",
                "occurring in the target could not reach the detector",
                "faces without scattering at least once. The scattered",
                "fragments, of course, did not produce coincidences in",
                "the detectors and in general have lower energies. The",
                "coincidence rates were 5 to 20 counts per hour.",
                "'Background' runs in which 232Th was bombarded",
                "yielded no coincidence counts in 11 hours."
              ]
            }
          ],
